Class SuggestedAssigneeBuilderBase

java.lang.Object
gw.api.assignment.SuggestedAssigneeBuilderBase
All Implemented Interfaces:
SuggestedAssigneeBuilder
public abstract class SuggestedAssigneeBuilderBase extends Object implements SuggestedAssigneeBuilder
Base implementation of SuggestedAssigneeBuilder, provides a skeleton implementation and utilities that should be useful to multiple implementations

  • Method Details

    • getSuggestedAssignees

      public Assignee[] getSuggestedAssignees()
      Returns a list of suggested assignees. This is a template method that calls addSuggestedAssignees(java.util.List,java.util.Set) to do the heavy listing. The template just sets up the result list, creates a set to keep track of items that are already added and then, providing there is anything to be assigned, calls into addSuggestedAssignees to actually construct the list.
      Specified by:
      getSuggestedAssignees in interface SuggestedAssigneeBuilder
      Returns:
      a list of suggested assignees

    • addSuggestedAssignees

      protected abstract void addSuggestedAssignees(List list, Set alreadyAdded)
      The main subclasser responsibility, actually builds the list of suggested assignees. The implementation should use the various add utilities to add new assignees to the given list and set.
      Parameters:
      list - the ordered result list, contains assignees
      alreadyAdded - set of assignees, to keep track of which have been

    • addLoggedInUser

      protected void addLoggedInUser(List list, Set usersAlreadyAded)
      Utility - adds the logged in user. Adds all user, group combinations where group is any group that both the logged in user belongs to AND one of the beans is assigned to. If no such group exists, then adds an entry for each group the user belongs to.
      Parameters:
      list - list to add to
      usersAlreadyAded - set of assignees that are aleardy added

    • addGroupSupervisor
